label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$M$", M, S);
draw(rightanglemark(A,M,B,10));
[/asy] We know that $BM = MC = \frac{BC}{2} = 5.$ Now we just simply apply the Pythagorean Theorem on the right triangle $\triangle ABM.$ \begin{align*}
AM^2 &= AB^2 - BM^2\\
AM^2 &= 8^2 - 5^2 = 39\\
AM &= \boxed{\sqrt{39}}
\end{align*}

